<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_8e282e86-1a06-4f8c-8d0c-65845467496f" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="WA"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>H9P2</sptc><title id="_1523c53c-6c34-4dcf-bda8-1a264a9f7c4d">Water loss prevention</title><archive-num>2019: WA 2.2(b)</archive-num><subclause id="_a035a537-b4ae-494c-92e9-593382fb0c2f" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7d5ac539-0b15-4708-9d55-60c3812494d4">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A building, including any water holding structure, must have features that, to the degree necessary, prevent excessive loss of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_cd4c3219-8c3e-49f8-a65a-12eb80294886" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> appropriate to—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_4b0d182d-281b-420c-8e15-85a6052fc083">the geographic location of the building; and</li><li id="_2070a1ab-2db6-4f66-a123-54dbe364c71d">the available <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_37638856-a55e-43b4-b8a4-48efce9f646a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> supply for the building; and</li><li id="_2cc78942-253e-4aa8-aed0-435af267361b">the function and use of the building; and</li><li id="_be992165-28d2-46b1-8fda-aa5ddfdb2655">the effects of permanent features such as topography, structures and buildings.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_8004b2e2-7787-4fe4-b915-c2a9d398e7cf"><callout-type ncc-info-type="application"/><p>WA H9P2 only applies to Class 1 buildings, associated Class 10a buildings and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_a0c7d6fc-97cc-4d08-b36e-75ee1d0b9e2c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pools</xref> associated with a Class 1 building.</p></callout></clause>